<br><br>In this article, <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/dr-richard-dune-blog" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);">Dr Richard Dune</span></i></a> will discuss how Ofsted’s role is crucial in ensuring that education and social care services in England meet national standards and are of the highest quality. Dr Dune will also examine the role, powers, and controversies surrounding Ofsted and how it can impact children’s education and care.
<br>
</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-edLa-Dd kzGYaw pf-25_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-kuVMvl bBmUMO pf-27_">What is the role of Ofsted?
</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_the_role_of_Ofsted_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_--min.jpg?v=1683190232" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_the_role_of_Ofsted_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_--min.jpg?v=1683190232 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_the_role_of_Ofsted_-_Dr_Richard_Dune_--min_500x.jpg?v=1683190232 320w" width="4096" height="2730" alt="What is the role of Ofsted? - Dr Richard Dune -" title="What is the role of Ofsted? - Dr Richard Dune -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-gplwNw cwEcYX pf-28_"/><p class="sc-iaJahb lhtKFo pf-29_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-kuVMvl bBmUMO pf-31_">The role of Ofsted is crucial in ensuring that all children and young people in England have access to high-quality education and care services that meet national standards. Ofsted’s powers to regulate and inspect organisations and services help achieve this aim by ensuring that the required criteria are met and that there is continuous improvement in education and social care services.
<br><br>Ofsted can act against organisations and services that fail to meet the required standards. The rating given to an organisation by Ofsted carries significant weight. It impacts its reputation and negatively affects the organisation, staff, children, and young people. This reinforces the importance of high-quality services that meet national standards.
<br>
